Class-Serializer

This module does its best efforts to serialize the in-memory state of a class
into runable code.

The most important thing, however is to keep in mind that this module is highly
experimental. There are no guarantees whatsoever about the generated code.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc Class::Serializer

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Class-Serializer

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Class-Serializer

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Class-Serializer

